# youtube-transcript skill

Extract transcripts from YouTube videos via the bundled `fetch-transcript.mjs` script. Supports both `youtube.com` and `youtu.be` URLs.

This skill:
- fetches captions first (fast)
- falls back to Whisper transcription via `yt-dlp` + Whisper-compatible API
- uses async mode for long videos
- saves a **summary** to `{{raw_dir}}`
- saves the **full transcript** to `{{transcripts_dir}}`

## Paths (set by Mission Control at install time)

- Summary dir: `{{raw_dir}}`
- Transcript dir: `{{transcripts_dir}}`
- Script path: `{{home_dir}}/.agents/skills/youtube-transcript/scripts/fetch-transcript.mjs`

## One-time setup

The script's npm deps install automatically on first use:

```bash
cd {{home_dir}}/.agents/skills/youtube-transcript/scripts
npm install --omit=dev
```

## Default workflow

1. **Start async job** to avoid timeouts:

```bash
node {{home_dir}}/.agents/skills/youtube-transcript/scripts/fetch-transcript.mjs \
  "<URL>" --async --save-dir "{{transcripts_dir}}"
```

This returns `{"jobId":"...","status":"queued"}`.

2. **Poll status** until `succeeded` or `failed`:

```bash
node {{home_dir}}/.agents/skills/youtube-transcript/scripts/fetch-transcript.mjs \
  --status <jobId>
```

3. **Fetch result**:

```bash
node {{home_dir}}/.agents/skills/youtube-transcript/scripts/fetch-transcript.mjs \
  --result <jobId>
```

Result JSON includes `text`, `title`, `videoId`, `source`, `language`, `saved_path` (the full transcript file in `{{transcripts_dir}}`).

## Summary generation

Write a **dynamic-length summary** to `{{raw_dir}}/{sort-prefix}-[{stars}]-{sanitized-title}-{YYYYMMDD}.md` using the heuristic below.

### Filename format

`0-[⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐]-{sanitized-title}-{YYYYMMDD}.md` (same prefix/star convention as link-capture)

### Content format

```markdown
---
url: <影片連結>
videoId: <VIDEO_ID>
title: <影片標題>
language: <語言>
type: youtube
rating: <1-5>
source: <captions|whisper>
transcript: "[[<transcript filename>]]"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
tags:
  - tag1
  - tag2
---

# {Video Title}

> [!summary] 一句話結論
> ...

## 重點整理

- 🎯 核心主題
- 💡 ...

## 行動 / 建議

- ...

---

完整逐字稿：[[<transcript filename>]]
```

Do **not** inline the full transcript into the summary file — it would bloat the note and Obsidian search. Link to the transcript file in `{{transcripts_dir}}` via an Obsidian wikilink.

### Length buckets (by transcript length)

- **S** (0–1,500 words / 0–4,000 zh chars): 1-sentence conclusion + ≤5 bullets + 0–3 actions
- **M** (1,500–4,500 words / 4,000–12,000 zh chars): 2–3 sentence summary + 8–12 bullets in 2–4 sections + 3–7 actions
- **L** (4,500–12,000 words): exec summary (3–6 sentences) + 3–6 themes × 2–4 bullets + 5–10 notable details + 5–10 actions
- **XL** (>12,000 words): 6–10 sentence summary + H3 outline with per-section bullets + 10–20 takeaways + ≤10 actions + optional "如果只看 5 分鐘" top-5

Caps: summary ≤ 8% of transcript length AND absolute cap (S: 300, M: 600, L/XL: 1200).

### Rules

- Prefer bullets over paragraphs
- Do not hallucinate — summarize what is in transcript
- Numbers/specs kept as-is; mark "可能/未確認" if unsure
- Whisper errors → summarize at a higher level, avoid quoting exact phrases
- **All summaries in Traditional Chinese**

## Completion report

Reply to the user with (in Traditional Chinese):

- 📺 Video title + URL
- 🎯 One-sentence conclusion
- 💡 3–5 bullet key takeaways
- 📁 Summary file path (raw_dir)
- 📁 Transcript file path (transcripts_dir)

## Whisper endpoint configuration

The script reads `WHISPER_BASE_URL` / `WHISPER_API_KEY` from environment.
Mission Control writes these into `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` under `skills.entries.youtube-transcript.env`:

- `WHISPER_BASE_URL`: `{{whisper_base_url}}`
- `WHISPER_API_KEY`: (from Mission Control settings)
